IBADAN – Mr. Kazeem Awojoodu, a re­porter of the Daily Independent Newspaper has been awarded with the Federal Ministry Of Interior Award Of Excellence. Awojoodu received the award alongside other jour­nalists in Ibadan, the Oyo State Capital through the Zonal Corps Commandant of the Nigeria Security and Civ­il Defence Corps (NSCDC), Deputy Commandant Gener­al Shem Obafaiye during the State Command end of the year party. Speaking on the purpose of the event that was held at the Command Headquarters Agodi Ibadan, the State Com­mandant of the NSCDC, Corps Commandant Iskilu Akinsan­ya said the event is an annual occasion organised purposely to celebrate gallant Officers that has made the Command proud. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! Commandant Iskilu stressed that the Command also do make use of the event to appreciate journalists that have been working through their reports for the progress of the command. He said, “without those jour­nalists that are projecting us to members of the public, most of our successful operations will not have been known. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION